# DockSec Cursor Rules

- STRICT: NEVER use "Cursor Agent", "AI Coding Assistant", or any AI-specific branding in code, comments, documentation, or commit messages.
- STRICT: NEVER add "Co-authored-by: Cursor" or any AI attribution to git commit messages. This is a hard requirement for project integrity.
- All code and comments must be professional, human-centric, and focused strictly on project functionality.
- Do not use em-dashes; use normal hyphens only.
- Do not use emojis in any communication or code.
